                <p>
                    In 2024, British Columbia received over <strong>8,000 nomination spots</strong>,
                    representing the peak of recent PNP allocations. This generous allotment allowed
                    the province to conduct frequent draws with lower minimum scores, benefiting
                    candidates across multiple occupation categories. The 2024 allocation enabled
                    BC to address critical labor shortages while maintaining robust immigration levels.
                </p>

